    content:
      "What Portals Do Most clinics offer secure websites or apps to:\r\n\r\n- View lab and imaging results\r\n- Message your care team\r\n- Request prescription refills\r\n- Schedule appointments\r\n- Download visit summaries Getting Started Ask front desk for signup instructions. You may need email verification and a one-time activation code from your visit paperwork. Reading Results Early Results may appear before your doctor reviews them. Abnormal flags are not always urgent — but note questions for your follow-up.\r\n\r\n:::warning\r\nPortals are not for emergencies. Call 911 or go to ER for immediate danger.\r\n::: Messaging Etiquette Include one clear question per message, your pharmacy if requesting refills, and allow 1–3 business days for replies. Privacy and Access Use strong passwords. Proxy access for caregivers may require separate authorization forms.",
    url: "/articles/patient-portal-basics",
