    category: "Conditions",
    categoryId: "glossary",
    content:
      "## What It Is\r\n\r\nDiabetes is a chronic disease that affects how your body turns food into energy. With diabetes, your body either does not make enough insulin or cannot use insulin properly, causing high blood sugar. Over time, high blood sugar can damage the heart, kidneys, nerves, and eyes if not managed.\r\n\r\n## Why It Matters\r\n\r\nDiabetes affects daily food choices, activity, foot care, eye exams, and medication timing. Early and consistent management prevents complications that develop silently over years.\r\n\r\n## Talk With Your Care Team\r\n\r\nAsk: What A1C or blood sugar targets are right for me? How often should I see an eye doctor and foot specialist, and what new symptoms should I report right away?",
