    content:
      "## What It Is\r\n\r\nAcute means sudden in onset and often short in duration. Acute illnesses or injuries develop quickly and may need prompt care — for example a broken bone, strep throat, or a panic attack. Acute is the opposite of chronic, which lasts months or years.\r\n\r\n## Why It Matters\r\n\r\nKnowing whether a problem is acute or chronic helps you set expectations for recovery time and urgency of follow-up. Acute symptoms that worsen quickly may need same-day care rather than waiting for a routine appointment.\r\n\r\n## Talk With Your Care Team\r\n\r\nAsk: Is this condition likely to resolve on its own, and what warning signs mean I should call sooner? How long should I wait before expecting improvement?",
