      "## What It Is\r\n\r\nA sign is an objective finding that others can observe or measure — such as a fever, rash, or high blood pressure reading. Signs differ from symptoms, which are what the patient feels and reports. Doctors use both signs and symptoms to make diagnoses.\r\n\r\n## Why It Matters\r\n\r\nSigns give objective evidence doctors measure — fever, blood pressure, lab flags. Knowing the difference from symptoms helps you describe both clearly at visits.\r\n\r\n## Talk With Your Care Team\r\n\r\nAsk: What signs will you monitor at follow-up, and can I track any of them at home? Which new signs should prompt a call before my next appointment?",
