      "## What It Is\r\n\r\nPrognosis is a doctor's best estimate of how a disease or condition is likely to progress over time — including chances of recovery, stability, or complications. Prognosis is not a guarantee; treatment, lifestyle, and new research can change outcomes. Always ask what factors affect your personal prognosis.\r\n\r\n## Why It Matters\r\n\r\nPrognosis helps plan work, family, and treatment intensity — but numbers are averages, not destiny. New therapies and personal factors can shift outcomes after the first conversation.\r\n\r\n## Talk With Your Care Team\r\n\r\nAsk: What factors most affect my individual outlook? What would change the prognosis if I follow treatment versus if I do not?",
